Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/17/02 9:24:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noob Troll Skald</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the input! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/unamuna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namuna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/17/02 9:34:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noob Troll Skald</span><hr size=1> Pretty solid advice from PFalcon.<br><br>My only variation, and it's pretty small, is the end Template.<br><br>Mine will be:<br>46Song/44Hammer/leftover Parry.<br><br>44 Weapon gives the 44weapon style (only style after comes at 50 spec), and with the +spec items and Realm Rank that will easily go over 50spec anyway and the leftover points will raise Parry.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/17/02 3:12:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noob Troll Skald</span><hr size=1> I disagree about the starting stat allocation. 10 str/con/cha looks best. Even for a troll lvl 50 when your str will be slightly over 200 (207 capped with +10 at creation), str&gt;dex imo. Con&gt;dex. Con&gt;cha. Str&gt;cha. None are so great as to give up 5 pts by raising something 15.<br><br>Charisma affects dd damage as much as str affects weapon damage. Since we have very high weapon spec and our dd's are on a 20 second timer we will do 3/4 of our damage with our weapons. Therefore str&gt;cha.<br><br>Con increases hits by ~3.5 per point at lvl 50. 10 points of con will give 35 hits and 10 points of cha will increase dd damage by 3.3%. Our dd's do about 400 damage combined so we would do an extra 13 points of damage with 10 points cha. Considering that 3 sets will completely deplete your power, that's only an extra 30 damage in an extended fight. Con&gt;cha, but it's close. Certainly cha/2 !&gt; con.<br><br>Dex is pretty useless relative to str/con/cha, even qui. It affects parry rate, and 1/2 evade rate. However, from what I've seen it has a very small effect.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/17/02 3:43:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noob Troll Skald</span><hr size=1> I think that any combination of Str/Con/Dex/Qui/Cha <br>is fine if it's in 10 or less blocks.  Choose what you feel you'd like to focus on.<br><br>STR: Weaponskill(dmg) and carry capacity<br>CON: HP and small amount of dmg reduction/hit<br>DEX: Contribute to parry rate and 1/2 evade<br>QUI: Faster weapon speed(more dmg/time) and 1/2 to evade.<br>CHA: DD damage (about 1:1 and 1:0.5 ratios for the highest 2 DDs at level 50)<br><br>Most common is Str/Con/Cha, but by no means would you be gimp'd otherwise.<br><br>-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=192.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=192.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=192.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=192.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=192.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=192.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="teamskaldfrm1">General Discussion<option value="teamskaldfrm6">Bug Forum - General<option value="teamskaldfrm7">Wish List<option value="teamskaldfrm9">Equipment Discussions<option value="teamskaldfrm10">RvR Discussions<option value="teamskaldfrm11">PvE Discussions<option value="teamskaldfrm12">Quest Dis